170
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:11,143
-That needs pressing.
-Okay.

171
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:14,897
But let's not forget Eric trades
commodities for a living.

172
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:19,610
A little competition right now
might increase my market value.

173
00:14:20,944 --> 00:14:24,865
Listen, my darling, I’m going
to be late. I’ll call you later, okay?

174
00:14:26,158 --> 00:14:27,534
Excuse me. Sorry.

175
00:14:27,701 --> 00:14:31,538
Could you just hold up those two
outfits that Dolce sent over earlier?

176
00:14:33,123 --> 00:14:35,000
These two?

177
00:14:35,876 --> 00:14:40,088
Well, I just simply can't tell
without the stockings.

178
00:14:41,507 --> 00:14:44,301
Could I ask you an enormous favour?

179
00:14:44,593 --> 00:14:49,556
I mean, I know this isn't your job,
and I’d never normally ask, but I’m so....

180
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:52,893
-It’s okay.
-You're such a doll.

181
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,104
Would you run down to Madison
and get me three pairs of pantyhose?

182
00:14:56,271 --> 00:14:59,942
-The concierge usually does that.
-Yes, but it will get lost in translation.

183
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:02,486
Please. You look like
you're someone...

184
00:15:02,653 --> 00:15:05,697
...who knows the difference
between taupe and caramel.

185
00:15:07,074 --> 00:15:10,035
-Okay.
-Thanks.

186
00:15:11,662 --> 00:15:13,705
Here. Thank you so much.

187
00:15:13,872 --> 00:15:15,916
-Okay.
-Oh, and sorry.

188
00:15:16,083 --> 00:15:19,086
Can you send someone else
to finish the unpacking, please?

189
00:15:19,253 --> 00:15:21,380
-Right away.
-Thanks.

190
00:15:21,839 --> 00:15:23,173
Bye.

191
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:25,926
Attention! Somebody's coming!

192
00:15:28,595 --> 00:15:31,056
-You think it's gonna rain?
-Maybe. It’s possible.

193
00:15:31,265 --> 00:15:32,599
-Hi, where's the fire?
-Nowhere.

194
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:34,852
I just got sent on an errand.
I’m already late.

195
00:15:35,018 --> 00:15:37,312
-Get these pressed for me?
-Sure, in my spare time.

196
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:39,314
By the way, two poodles
raiding your cart.

197
00:15:39,481 --> 00:15:40,732
-What?
-Can't be late for Ty!

198
00:15:49,074 --> 00:15:52,119
Mary Anne, if you don't wear
that dress, I’m gonna come over.

199
00:15:52,286 --> 00:15:55,622
I’m gonna go in your closet.
I’m gonna put it on for you.

200
00:15:56,623 --> 00:15:58,208
Wait. Hold on a sec.

201
00:15:58,542 --> 00:16:00,752
Excuse me, miss?
Where are you going?

202
00:16:00,919 --> 00:16:03,255
-In back to see if Carrie's here.
-Carrie's not here.

203
00:16:03,422 --> 00:16:05,090
So could you just step away?

204
00:16:05,257 --> 00:16:06,425
Away.

205
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:09,595
Away. Away from there.
Thank you.

206
00:16:09,845 --> 00:16:13,223
Hi. Sorry. Okay, so you go first.

207
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:16,643
No, you! No, you.

208
00:16:17,019 --> 00:16:18,478
Get out.

209
00:16:18,645 --> 00:16:22,065
-Get out.
-Excuse me, just a moment.

210
00:16:22,232 --> 00:16:24,359
You know what? I have customers,
so go on quick.

211
00:16:24,526 --> 00:16:27,738
Yeah. Then what?

212
00:16:27,905 --> 00:16:29,406
No, he didn't.

213
00:16:29,656 --> 00:16:31,783
-No, he didn't.
-Can I just ask you one question?

214
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:36,830
You know what, ma'am?
You have to wait. Okay?

215
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:40,584
What? No, a maid.

216
00:16:40,959 --> 00:16:42,377
-I don't know.
-Yo.

217
00:16:42,544 --> 00:16:44,671
