01:00:46,978 --> 01:00:49,355
Just charge it to my room.

950
01:00:49,522 --> 01:00:50,815
Yes, ma'am.

951
01:00:50,982 --> 01:00:53,943
Come on, Rach. Ghastly man!

952
01:00:54,110 --> 01:00:56,571
I am terrified to ask
what that was about.

953
01:00:56,738 --> 01:00:58,948
I think, being dumped.

954
01:00:59,157 --> 01:01:02,285
-Can I get your autograph?
-Amber? Is that your name?

955
01:01:02,452 --> 01:01:04,620
-Amber's your name.
-How you doing?

956
01:01:04,829 --> 01:01:08,708
Get in the car! Get in the car!

957
01:01:10,043 --> 01:01:13,504
-Did she see us?
-Yeah. No. You're fine. All's clear.

958
01:01:13,671 --> 01:01:15,673
-It’s fine.
-How did this happen?

959
01:01:15,840 --> 01:01:18,009
I think she's very attractive.

960
01:01:18,176 --> 01:01:21,304
I had her checked out.
She comes from a family with money...

961
01:01:21,471 --> 01:01:23,931
...politically neutral and
has no naked pictures.

962
01:01:24,098 --> 01:01:26,184
That woman wasn't
the woman I wanted.

963
01:01:26,351 --> 01:01:29,395
I don't know what to say.
I talked to the hotel manager.

964
01:01:29,562 --> 01:01:33,232
That's the only Caroline Lane
staying in the Park Suite.

965
01:01:33,399 --> 01:01:35,735
Wait. There she is.

966
01:01:36,152 --> 01:01:38,071
That's her. Cordell, pull over.

967
01:01:42,492 --> 01:01:45,495
-Hey, wait! Ty! Caroline!
-Hey, Chris!

968
01:01:45,703 --> 01:01:48,206
-Hey. How's it going, Ty?
-Okay.

969
01:01:48,373 --> 01:01:49,707
-How you doing?
-Good.

970
01:01:49,874 --> 01:01:53,878
You want to hear something strange?
I invited you to lunch, and you came...

971
01:01:54,045 --> 01:01:55,296
...only it wasn't you.

972
01:01:55,838 --> 01:01:57,840
So, what happened?

973
01:01:58,049 --> 01:02:02,595
-I don't know what you mean.
-Are you still staying at the Beresford?

974
01:02:02,762 --> 01:02:06,766
No, we actually moved uptown.
You know, uptown.

975
01:02:06,933 --> 01:02:09,686
Hop in. We're going
to the Tremont Housing Projects.

976
01:02:09,852 --> 01:02:12,855
-We can drop you at the Upper East?
-Yeah, Mom!

977
01:02:13,064 --> 01:02:17,527
No. Remember, we're going to a party
just a few blocks away, so we'll walk.

978
01:02:17,735 --> 01:02:20,321
-So how do I get a hold of you?
-Her cell's 9-1-7--

979
01:02:20,989 --> 01:02:22,657
How about I call you?

980
01:02:22,824 --> 01:02:25,994
lf you want to get in touch with him,
call this number.

981
01:02:26,160 --> 01:02:28,955
That's my card.
What's your last name, hon?

982
01:02:29,122 --> 01:02:31,624
-Ventura. What's yours?
-Spanish?

983
01:02:31,791 --> 01:02:35,128
-Jerry Spanish?
-No, Siegel. We have to go.

984
01:02:35,294 --> 01:02:37,839
-So do we.
-Use that number. Call anytime.

985
01:02:38,006 --> 01:02:39,382
-All right.
-Don't be shy.

986
01:02:39,549 --> 01:02:43,636
-You're late. You have to give a speech.
-In the Bronx?

987
01:02:43,803 --> 01:02:45,888
-On what?
-Housing projects.

988
01:02:46,055 --> 01:02:47,056
Really?

989
01:02:47,765 --> 01:02:50,852
You're telling people
in the Bronx about the projects?

990
01:02:51,019 --> 01:02:53,271
No, I’m just gonna
take the press up there...

991
01:02:53,438 --> 01:02:55,773
...and shine light
on the living conditions.

992
01:02:56,858 --> 01:02:59,610
-Interesting.
-Yeah, we think so. Shall we? Okay?

993
01:02:59,777 --> 01:03:01,654
-Bye.
-What are you not saying?

994
01:03:01,821 --> 01:03:04,073
-Nothing.
-Tell me.

995
01:03:07,035 --> 01:03:10,079
Maybe you should spend
real time in the projects...

996
01:03:10,288 --> 01:03:14,042
...and then you wouldn't have to make up
speeches and memorize them.

997
01:03:14,208 --> 01:03:17,587
You know, it would be coming
from someplace real.

998
01:03:17,754 --> 01:03:20,256
And how would you know? I mean....

999
01:03:20,423 --> 01:03:22,925
Because I grew up there.

1000
01:03:23,134 --> 01:03:26,095
I lived in a four-block radius
my whole life.

1001
01:03:26,304 --> 01:03:28,264
Bye.

1002
01:03:30,808 --> 01:03:33,436
Okay, let's go. Come on.

1003
01:03:35,313 --> 01:03:37,315
-Chris!
-What?

1004
01:03:37,482 --> 01:03:41,778
Shall we? Okay? Let's go.
Gotta go. Gotta go. Gotta go.

1005
01:03:43,988 --> 01:03:45,156
Who the hell is she?

1006
01:03:45,323 --> 01:03:51,245
I’ll tell you who she isn't. She isn't like
anyone I’ve met. And she isn't a phoney.

1007
01:03:51,412 --> 01:03:55,958
I’ll make you a deal. You want me
at the benefit? Then get her to go.

1008
01:03:56,125 --> 01:04:00,213
I swear to God, I’ll shake any
part of Maddox's body you want.

1009
01:04:02,590 --> 01:04:04,467
Deal?

1010
01:04:04,967 --> 01:04:07,136
Deal. All right, sure. Okay.

1011
01:04:14,811 --> 01:04:16,312
Okay, get in.

1012
01:04:21,192 --> 01:04:24,195
So for right now, with the review
and everything going on...

1013
01:04:24,362 --> 01:04:26,656
...we need to be extra careful,
all right?

1014
01:04:26,864 --> 01:04:29,575
That means no coming up
in the elevator to see me.

1015
01:04:29,742 --> 01:04:31,953
And no Chris Marshall.

1016
01:04:32,120 --> 01:04:35,373
-It’s not like you're breaking some law.
-Hey, I mean it.

1017
01:04:35,540 --> 01:04:36,916
lf you see him....

1018
01:04:37,083 --> 01:04:41,879
-I’ll make like a baby and head out first.
-Thank you. Go to bed, okay?

1019
01:04:42,046 --> 01:04:44,924
-Good night, Ma.
-Bye, baby.

1020
01:04:50,388 --> 01:04:51,723
Heads up!

1021
01:04:51,889 --> 01:04:55,018
The Chinese delegation will be
checking into the Lexington Suite.

1022
01:04:55,226 --> 01:04:59,063
Please note the television channel
needs to be set to one of the Chinese....

1023
01:04:59,230 --> 01:05:00,815
Oh, my God. Hide me.

1024
01:05:01,607 --> 01:05:04,736
The Shapiros have requested
an early check-in.

1025
01:05:04,902 --> 01:05:07,113
So we'll put them in the Dior Suite.

1026
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:08,781
Yes, sir?

1027
01:05:08,948 --> 01:05:10,867
-They're in the hall.
-What are they doing?

1028
01:05:11,034 --> 01:05:13,703
-He's got something in his hands.
-Does it look serious?

1029
01:05:13,870 --> 01:05:15,747
Calm down, it's just a letter.

1030
01:05:15,913 --> 01:05:17,874
-Find that girl.
-Certainly.

1031
01:05:18,082 --> 01:05:19,042
-He's coming.
-Be cool.

1032
01:05:19,250 --> 01:05:22,670
He's walking. Get out of here.
He's out of here.

1033
01:05:22,837 --> 01:05:24,797
Thank you very much. That will be all.

1034
01:05:40,897 --> 01:05:43,107
Now....

1035
01:05:43,274 --> 01:05:46,819
Are you truly interested
in management?

1036
01:05:46,986 --> 01:05:49,405
Yes, very much, sir.

1037
01:05:50,281 --> 01:05:55,161
Then I suggest that you go
to the Met tonight...

1038
01:05:55,328 --> 01:06:00,375
...and end all association
with Chris Marshall.

1039
01:06:01,084 --> 01:06:03,169
At least until you're a manager.

1040
01:06:03,628 --> 01:06:05,672
Then you can make your own rules.

1041
01:06:06,422 --> 01:06:08,424
I’ll make sure your shift is covered.

1042
01:06:24,399 --> 01:06:26,067
-Mari.
-What happened?

1043
01:06:26,234 --> 01:06:29,904
-You can still be a manager, right?
-Yeah, if I break it off with Chris.

1044
01:06:30,071 --> 01:06:33,282
Break what off? No offence,
sweetheart. What planet are you on?

1045
01:06:33,491 --> 01:06:35,118
You don't get it. None of you.

1046
01:06:35,326 --> 01:06:37,370
There was something
different about him.

1047
01:06:37,537 --> 01:06:38,788
Yeah, it's called money.

1048
01:06:38,997 --> 01:06:40,957
-No, it's called--
-Don't say, “love.”

1049
01:06:41,165 --> 01:06:43,126
-Don't let her say it.
-She's going to.

1050
01:06:43,334 --> 01:06:45,336
We connected, you know....

1051
01:06:45,503 --> 01:06:48,798
-I felt it. Ty felt it too.
-Snap out of it, all right?

1052
01:06:49,007 --> 01:06:51,801
You are not in love with this man.
He is not in love with you.

1053
01:06:51,968 --> 01:06:54,220
You have no connections,
affiliations or loyalties.

1054
01:06:54,387 --> 01:06:57,390
You're from two different worlds.
Do you hear me?

1055
01:06:57,557 --> 01:06:59,767
-I hear you.
-Me too.

1056
01:06:59,934 --> 01:07:01,519
I don't know.

1057
01:07:01,686 --> 01:07:04,731
Come on, Maris, you....

1058
01:07:04,897 --> 01:07:06,858
You could be manager!

1059
01:07:07,025 --> 01:07:09,819
Think of it, girl. One of us...

1060
01:07:10,028 --> 01:07:11,988
...out there!

1061
01:07:12,196 --> 01:07:13,614
In a blazer.

1062
01:07:13,781 --> 01:07:15,867
Yeah.

1063
01:07:16,868 --> 01:07:19,037
I don't have anything
to wear to this thing.

1064
01:07:19,203 --> 01:07:22,915
-Honey, look, it's not what you got.
-Baby, it's who you know.

1065
01:07:23,082 --> 01:07:25,793
-And what they got.
-You got it?

1066
01:07:25,960 --> 01:07:29,255
When you're a manager, your first
order of business is to get us--

1067
01:07:29,422 --> 01:07:32,008
Raises!

1068
01:08:56,134 --> 01:08:58,052
All right, Ty, focus.

1069
01:08:58,219 --> 01:08:59,679
Eyes forward.

1070
01:08:59,846 --> 01:09:02,849
Once more.
This is the Harry Winston....

1071
01:09:03,016 --> 01:09:05,727
Wreath necklace. Worth more
than I’ll see in 10 lifetimes.

1072
01:09:05,893 --> 01:09:09,605
Good. And if it leaves her neck
at any time, you'll....

1073
01:09:09,814 --> 01:09:13,109
Be put up for adoption
while my mom....

1074
01:09:14,944 --> 01:09:16,821
-Rots in prison!
-Excellent.

1075
01:09:21,492 --> 01:09:23,202
-You want to say hi to Harry?
-Harry.

1076
01:09:23,369 --> 01:09:25,455
What do you need?
Tell me what you need.

1077
01:09:25,663 --> 01:09:26,956
Just your support, Harry.

1078
01:09:27,165 --> 01:09:29,334
What about a cameo
on Saturday Night Live?

1079
01:09:29,500 --> 01:09:31,544
-Let's wait on that.
-I’m calling Lorne.

1080
01:09:31,711 --> 01:09:33,880
-It’s nice to see you.
-Good to see you.

1081
01:09:45,016 --> 01:09:46,809
-There they are. See them?
-I see them.

1082
01:09:47,018 --> 01:09:50,563
We're going to line up Maddox's
support and get Grey's endorsement.

1083
01:09:50,730 --> 01:09:52,273
Just go and get it over with.

1084
01:09:52,440 --> 01:09:56,027
-Is she here?
-She'll be here. She'll be here.

1085
01:09:58,821 --> 01:10:00,657
-Have fun, Ma.
-Thanks.

1086
01:10:00,823 --> 01:10:05,203
Listen, be good. Go to bed when
Steph tells you. No negotiating. Okay?

1087
01:10:05,370 --> 01:10:06,704
Oh, God.

1088
01:10:06,871 --> 01:10:09,082
I can't breathe.

1089
01:10:09,707 --> 01:10:12,251
What am I doing here, Steph?
This is all a lie.

1090
01:10:12,418 --> 01:10:15,046
No, honey.
It’s more like a dream, you know?

1091
01:10:15,213 --> 01:10:17,507
For one night,
you're living it for all of us.

1092
01:10:17,674 --> 01:10:20,551
Don't think about tomorrow.
Just think about tonight.

1093
01:10:20,718 --> 01:10:22,637
Tonight, the maid is a lie.

1094
01:10:22,804 --> 01:10:27,100
And this, this is who you really are.

1095
01:10:51,541 --> 01:10:52,709
What do you think?

1096
01:10:52,917 --> 01:10:55,461
I think we have a lot
of issues to talk about.

1097
01:10:56,170 --> 01:10:57,380
-Let's get together.
-Good.

1098
01:10:57,588 --> 01:11:01,050
Excuse me. I think now's
the perfect time if you'd like to....

1099
01:11:01,259 --> 01:11:03,678
Oh, my God, Jerry.
Look who's here.

1100
01:11:03,845 --> 01:11:07,890
Lovely of you,
but I don't think I’ll be in town.

1101
01:11:08,099 --> 01:11:09,976
I’m gonna bring him over here.

1102
01:11:10,143 --> 01:11:12,562
No. She should be here by now.
She's not coming.

1103
01:11:12,729 --> 01:11:15,857
-She'll be here. She'll be here.
-She'd better be, Jerry.

1104
01:11:53,645 --> 01:11:55,605
You're beautiful.

1105
01:11:56,814 --> 01:11:59,025
So are you.

1106
01:12:03,821 --> 01:12:06,115
Thank you for being here.

1107
01:12:08,951 --> 01:12:12,038
I only came to tell you that this...

1108
01:12:12,205 --> 01:12:15,249
...you and me, can't go
anywhere beyond this evening.

1109
01:12:15,416 --> 01:12:17,043
It just can't.

1110
01:12:18,378 --> 01:12:21,255
Well, then, you should've
worn a different dress.

1111
01:12:26,344 --> 01:12:28,262
Want to dance?

1112
01:12:51,953 --> 01:12:55,123
You have to listen.
I know you're used to getting your way.

1113
01:12:55,289 --> 01:12:57,709
Yeah, until I met you.

1114
01:12:59,544 --> 01:13:02,588
There's millions of women who are
dying for you to look their way.

1115
01:13:02,755 --> 01:13:06,300
Yeah? Then why are you
making me work so hard?

1116
01:13:06,467 --> 01:13:09,137
Chris? Hi.
Maddox is open.

1117
01:13:09,304 --> 01:13:11,431
So why don't you go over,
two minutes.

1118
01:13:11,597 --> 01:13:14,017
-Jerry. I’m here--
-I’ll take over. I know.

1119
01:13:17,270 --> 01:13:20,189
-Oh, Chris. Hi.
-Hello.

1120
01:13:21,733 --> 01:13:25,820
-What a night. I mean, who isn't here?
-Right.

1121
01:13:26,404 --> 01:13:30,408
Do I need to know something
that I don't know already?

1122
01:13:31,367 --> 01:13:35,079
Well, that sounds like something
between you and your God, Jerry.

1123
01:13:35,246 --> 01:13:37,457
I like a good mystery, you know.

1124
01:13:37,623 --> 01:13:40,251
But not where his girlfriends
are concerned.

1125
01:13:40,418 --> 01:13:41,919
I’m not his girlfriend.

1126
01:13:42,086 --> 01:13:44,630
Well, whatever.
I just need him focused.

1127
01:13:44,797 --> 01:13:46,549
-Sorry about that.
-Not at all.

1128
01:13:46,758 --> 01:13:48,384
-May I cut in?
-You certainly may.

1129
01:13:48,593 --> 01:13:52,639
Where were we?
Right about here, wasn't it?

1130
01:13:52,805 --> 01:13:57,060
You better do what you're supposed
to because Jerry thinks I distract you.

1131
01:13:57,268 --> 01:14:02,982
Wait, wait. Never, never start
a sentence with “Jerry thinks.”

1132
01:14:03,149 --> 01:14:06,527
No, but you should do the right thing.

1133
01:14:09,322 --> 01:14:11,282
Why are you smiling?

1134
01:14:11,449 --> 01:14:16,204
Nothing, just until this minute,
I didn't know what that was.

1135
01:14:16,371 --> 01:14:18,289
-But I do now.
-You do what?

1136
01:14:18,456 --> 01:14:20,708
-Don't go anywhere.
-Chris, I didn't mean--

1137
01:14:20,875 --> 01:14:23,878
I’ll be right back.
I’ll be right back.

1138
01:14:46,067 --> 01:14:47,652
Excuse me.

1139
01:14:47,819 --> 01:14:49,862
Excuse me.
Haven't we met?

1140
01:14:50,029 --> 01:14:53,533
-I’m Caroline Lane and you're...?
-Sotheby's Caroline Lane?

1141
01:14:53,700 --> 01:14:55,660
-Yes.
-It’s wonderful to see you again.

1142
01:14:55,827 --> 01:14:59,998
I just knew we knew each other.
I never forget a face. Wow!

1143
01:15:00,164 --> 01:15:02,667
Is that a Harry Winston wreath?

1144
01:15:02,834 --> 01:15:05,628
They haven't made
that design since the late '60s.

1145
01:15:05,795 --> 01:15:08,423
You're very good.
Excuse me, I have to go.

1146
01:15:08,589 --> 01:15:11,551
Listen, just between us girls.

1147
01:15:11,718 --> 01:15:14,679
Are you here with Chris?

1148
01:15:14,846 --> 01:15:17,140
-Can you keep a secret?
-Of course.

1149
01:15:17,348 --> 01:15:20,184
Good. So can l.

1150
01:15:28,693 --> 01:15:30,653
Caroline.

1151
01:15:33,573 --> 01:15:35,533
Caroline.

1152
01:15:38,453 --> 01:15:39,829
Caroline.

1153
01:15:39,996 --> 01:15:42,707
-Do you have somewhere else to be?
-I have to leave.

1154
01:15:42,874 --> 01:15:44,500
You're not leaving. You're running.

1155
01:15:44,709 --> 01:15:47,670
What I can't figure out is, are you
running towards something you want?

1156
01:15:47,837 --> 01:15:51,382
Or are you running away from
something you're afraid to want?

1157
01:15:51,883 --> 01:15:54,218
Look, I’ve made
so many mistakes already.

1158
01:15:54,385 --> 01:15:58,765
-I just don't want to make it worse.
-You won't. I promise.

1159
01:15:59,223 --> 01:16:02,101
There's something
you don't know, okay?

1160
01:16:02,977 --> 01:16:04,604
Oh, God. How do I tell you this?

1161
01:16:05,438 --> 01:16:09,901
-The first time you saw me, I was--
-You were mesmerizing.

1162
01:16:22,830 --> 01:16:25,625
lf tonight is all we have...

1163
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:29,462
...stay. Please.

1164
01:18:14,025 --> 01:18:16,444
It’s over, baby.

1165
01:18:28,373 --> 01:18:30,500
Hi, honey.

1166
01:18:31,125 --> 01:18:33,002
I’m good.

1167
01:18:33,169 --> 01:18:35,338
At work.

1168
01:18:35,546 --> 01:18:40,176
Listen, abuela's gonna be there in about
10 minutes, and I’ll be home at 6.

1169
01:18:40,343 --> 01:18:42,845
Did you and Steph have a good time?

1170
01:18:43,054 --> 01:18:44,639
Yeah?

1171
01:18:59,070 --> 01:19:00,738
What are you gonna do in Buffalo?

1172
01:19:00,905 --> 01:19:04,117
Well, my plan is to sort of
accidentally bump into him.

1173
01:19:04,283 --> 01:19:07,495
-I mean, do you think that's too obvious?
-No.

1174
01:19:11,958 --> 01:19:14,919
-A Harry Winston wreath?
-Morning.

1175
01:19:15,628 --> 01:19:18,381
Isn’t that that maid?

1176
01:19:20,258 --> 01:19:23,386
I mean, where would a maid get
that necklace? I thought maybe--

1177
01:19:23,553 --> 01:19:27,223
I’ll fast-forward through this, and you
just point her out if you see her.

1178
01:19:29,100 --> 01:19:32,312
Oh, wait, could you just
go back on that bit?

1179
01:19:35,356 --> 01:19:39,402
I mean, it could be her.

1180
01:19:39,610 --> 01:19:43,197
Let's just--
Can we just go forward?

1181
01:19:47,118 --> 01:19:49,912
Wait! That's my Dolce coat!

1182
01:19:50,079 --> 01:19:53,416
-How could you have missed that?
-I’m sorry, sir.

1183
01:19:56,294 --> 01:19:58,421
I’ll have maintenance
get there with a plunger.

1184
01:19:58,588 --> 01:20:02,008
And I’ll call the pharmacy to see
if they have something for that.

1185
01:20:02,175 --> 01:20:07,263
Excuse me, sir. Mr. Bextrum wants
to see both of you in the Park Suite.

1186
01:20:29,410 --> 01:20:31,245
Lionel. Marisa.

1187
01:20:31,412 --> 01:20:35,500
Oh. Well, that's interesting.
She told me her name was Maria.

1188
01:20:35,667 --> 01:20:38,461
I thought it would be impolite
to correct you.

1189
01:20:38,628 --> 01:20:41,923
And I suppose you think
it's polite to steal people's clothes?

1190
01:20:44,050 --> 01:20:46,636
-I didn't steal--
-Miss Ventura, Mr. Bextrum has spent...

1191
01:20:46,803 --> 01:20:50,056
...30 minutes trying to persuade
Miss Lane not to press charges.

1192
01:20:50,223 --> 01:20:52,433
I suggest you say as little as possible.

1193
01:20:52,600 --> 01:20:54,435
We have it all on video.

1194
01:20:54,602 --> 01:20:56,270
Was everything returned?

1195
01:20:57,188 --> 01:21:00,066
-Yes, sir.
-Oh, Chris, I’m terribly sorry...

1196
01:21:00,233 --> 01:21:03,569
...to interrupt you. We thought you
should know what was going on.

1197
01:21:03,736 --> 01:21:06,406
-What is going on?
-The woman you thought was a guest...

1198
01:21:06,572 --> 01:21:08,866
...on this floor is the maid on this floor.

1199
01:21:09,033 --> 01:21:10,284
Aren't you, Marisa?

1200
01:21:10,451 --> 01:21:12,662
No. Wait, her name is Caroline.

1201
01:21:12,829 --> 01:21:16,958
No, Chris, darling, that's my name.
She steals clothes, identities--

1202
01:21:17,125 --> 01:21:21,004
What the hell's happening here?
Why are you dressed that way?

1203
01:21:22,338 --> 01:21:24,132
Caroline?

1204
01:21:26,217 --> 01:21:27,844
Is this true?

1205
01:21:34,767 --> 01:21:36,436
Yeah, it is.

1206
01:21:36,894 --> 01:21:40,857
Jesus Christ! The press is gonna
have a field day with this one.

1207
01:21:41,065 --> 01:21:42,900
There's no reason to involve the press.

1208
01:21:43,067 --> 01:21:45,194
How will you prevent her
from speaking?

1209
01:21:45,403 --> 01:21:47,322
This would never happen
at the Four Seasons.

1210
01:21:47,488 --> 01:21:50,533
I can assure you it has never
happened here before either.

1211
01:21:50,742 --> 01:21:54,787
Lionel, you are slipping. You should've
noticed something. I am disappointed.

1212
01:21:54,954 --> 01:21:57,623
Please, Mr. Bextrum,
he had nothing to do with this.

1213
01:21:57,790 --> 01:22:00,293
Of course, sir. I understand.

1214
01:22:00,460 --> 01:22:03,838
We'll talk about this later.
Miss Ventura, you no longer work here.

1215
01:22:04,005 --> 01:22:05,923
Go to security,
hand in your passes...

1216
01:22:06,090 --> 01:22:08,384
...and you'll be escorted
from the building.

1217
01:22:09,927 --> 01:22:12,680
-Yes, sir.
-Is that really necessary?

1218
01:22:12,847 --> 01:22:15,391
Chris, let the man do his job, okay?

1219
01:22:15,600 --> 01:22:17,727
Oh, Chris.

1220
01:22:17,894 --> 01:22:22,565
Oh, Chris. I can't help but feel
that this is partly my fault.

1221
01:22:22,732 --> 01:22:24,692
It isn't. Spare yourself.

1222
01:22:24,859 --> 01:22:26,527
At least let me buy you lunch.

1223
01:22:26,694 --> 01:22:30,573
After all, we've only got each other
to get through this humiliation.

1224
01:22:30,740 --> 01:22:35,703
Caroline, the first lunch was a mistake.
A second would be complete torture.

1225
01:22:36,204 --> 01:22:38,247
Drinks, then?

1226
01:22:38,456 --> 01:22:42,377
I need your nametag, passkey
and your ID card.

1227
01:22:42,543 --> 01:22:46,297
-Sorry, Marisa, but I have to.
-I understand.

1228
01:22:47,465 --> 01:22:49,926
God, don't tell me
they fired you over this too.

1229
01:22:50,134 --> 01:22:51,678
No.

1230
01:22:51,844 --> 01:22:55,682
Actually, I made a decision
a moment ago.

1231
01:22:55,848 --> 01:22:57,767
It was long overdue.

1232
01:22:59,435 --> 01:23:01,270
You quit?

1233
01:23:01,479 --> 01:23:03,439
Sometimes...

1234
01:23:03,606 --> 01:23:08,611
...we're forced in directions that we
ought to have found for ourselves.

1235
01:23:09,320 --> 01:23:11,114
Thank you.

1236
01:23:11,489 --> 01:23:14,575
Thanks, Keef. Bye.

1237
01:23:15,201 --> 01:23:17,787
To serve people...

1238
01:23:17,996 --> 01:23:20,623
...takes dignity and intelligence.

1239
01:23:20,790 --> 01:23:24,669
But remember,
they're only people with money.

1240
01:23:24,836 --> 01:23:29,632
And although we serve them,
we are not their servants.

1241
01:23:29,799 --> 01:23:35,305
What we do, Miss Ventura,
does not define who we are.

1242
01:23:35,513 --> 01:23:40,810
What defines us is how
well we rise after falling.

1243
01:23:44,355 --> 01:23:47,650
I think you'll make a wonderful
manager someday.

1244
01:23:50,111 --> 01:23:54,324
And it's been my great honour
to have worked with you.

1245
01:24:12,550 --> 01:24:14,344
Marisa?

1246
01:24:14,510 --> 01:24:17,555
Marisa! Caroline! Marisa!
I don't know which name to use.

1247
01:24:17,722 --> 01:24:19,682
Marisa.

1248
01:24:19,849 --> 01:24:21,643
I don't get it. What just happened?

1249
01:24:21,809 --> 01:24:23,478
What don't you get? I’m the maid.

1250
01:24:23,645 --> 01:24:26,564
What was all this, some kind of bet?

1251
01:24:26,731 --> 01:24:28,650
A little game of what, get-the-guests?

1252
01:24:28,816 --> 01:24:31,277
I was trying on her clothes,
and you were there...

1253
01:24:31,444 --> 01:24:33,655
...and you invited
me out, and everything--

1254
01:24:33,821 --> 01:24:36,491
And you thought you had to lie
to keep me interested?

1255
01:24:36,658 --> 01:24:37,909
Who's kidding who here?

1256
01:24:38,076 --> 01:24:40,995
Think you would've looked at me
if you knew I was the maid?

1257
01:24:41,162 --> 01:24:42,163
-Well....
-Come on.

1258
01:24:42,330 --> 01:24:44,248
With respect for
your big-hearted politics...

1259
01:24:44,415 --> 01:24:47,835
-...l don't think so, Mr. Assemblyman.
-You didn't give me a chance.

1260
01:24:48,002 --> 01:24:52,173
You stand on your soapbox, judging
everyone, so sure they're judging you.

1261
01:24:52,340 --> 01:24:54,050
And you think they're not?

1262
01:24:54,217 --> 01:24:57,136
Come on. Half the time, I’m
a stereotype they make fun of.

1263
01:24:57,303 --> 01:25:00,765
The other half of the time, I’m
invisible. Maybe that's the point.

1264
01:25:00,932 --> 01:25:04,644
The first time you saw me, I was cleaning
your bathroom, only you didn't see me.

1265
01:25:04,811 --> 01:25:07,522
Was I supposed to introduce
myself while taking a leak?

1266
01:25:07,689 --> 01:25:10,108
-You can't nail me for that.
-What are you doing?

1267
01:25:10,274 --> 01:25:11,401
Not now, Jerry. Just--

1268
01:25:11,567 --> 01:25:13,069
-Go.
-You might as well sell tickets.

1269
01:25:13,277 --> 01:25:14,570
-I don't care.
-You care.

1270
01:25:16,489 --> 01:25:19,409
-No. No. No. No.
-Marisa.

1271
01:25:19,575 --> 01:25:21,077
I just want the truth.

1272
01:25:25,206 --> 01:25:27,709
All right, you want the truth?

1273
01:25:30,211 --> 01:25:33,631
There was a part of me
that wanted to see what it felt like...

1274
01:25:33,798 --> 01:25:37,760
...to have someone like you look
at me the way you did, just once.

1275
01:25:40,680 --> 01:25:42,390
And I’m sorry.

1276
01:25:42,557 --> 01:25:44,142
Truly.

1277
01:25:44,309 --> 01:25:47,937
lf I could rewind the past week,
I would.

1278
01:25:50,064 --> 01:25:51,858
Was any of it real?

1279
01:25:54,777 --> 01:25:57,280
Yeah, it was real.

1280
01:25:58,448 --> 01:26:02,285
It was so real it made me wonder
how I was ever gonna give you up.

1281
01:26:05,246 --> 01:26:09,917
But I had to give you up.
That was the plan.

1282
01:26:12,670 --> 01:26:15,048
And then....

1283
01:26:15,214 --> 01:26:17,634
Last night...

1284
01:26:18,968 --> 01:26:21,054
...l couldn't.

1285
01:28:12,081 --> 01:28:16,544
Rosalie from personnel called.
We expected you hours ago.

1286
01:28:16,711 --> 01:28:17,962
Hi, baby.

1287
01:28:18,129 --> 01:28:20,131
She told me what happened.

1288
01:28:20,298 --> 01:28:23,134
Hey, Ma. You okay?

1289
01:28:23,301 --> 01:28:25,428
Scoot over, let me see your homework.

1290
01:28:25,595 --> 01:28:27,055
I don't know what to say.

1291
01:28:27,221 --> 01:28:30,099
What are we gonna do for dinner?
You hungry, sweetie?

1292
01:28:30,266 --> 01:28:32,393
Will you look at me?

1293
01:28:32,560 --> 01:28:35,855
No. I’m gonna take a bath.

1294
01:28:41,861 --> 01:28:43,696
Don't, Mom.

1295
01:28:43,863 --> 01:28:47,367
What were you thinking,
going out with someone like that?

1296
01:28:47,533 --> 01:28:49,077
Someone like what?

1297
01:28:50,495 --> 01:28:52,455
Chris Marshall.

1298
01:28:52,622 --> 01:28:55,416
You had to pretend to be somebody
so he'd go out with you?

1299
01:28:55,583 --> 01:28:58,586
Where is your pride, Marisa?

1300
01:28:58,753 --> 01:29:01,172
People like you make people
like him a God.

1301
01:29:01,339 --> 01:29:04,384
Why, because he's rich? White?
He has things we don't have...

1302
01:29:04,550 --> 01:29:06,469
...that we don't want to dream about?

1303
01:29:06,636 --> 01:29:10,306
It must really burn you that I think
I have the right to go out with him.

1304
01:29:10,515 --> 01:29:12,976
You don't.

1305
01:29:13,267 --> 01:29:16,479
Ty, go to your room
and finish your homework, please.

1306
01:29:19,190 --> 01:29:21,985
-What happened to you?
-Don't speak to me like that.

1307
01:29:22,193 --> 01:29:24,988
I am not the one
who lost her job today.

1308
01:29:25,196 --> 01:29:27,407
No, I did. I messed up.

1309
01:29:27,573 --> 01:29:31,703
Okay? It’s all my fault. You know what?
It’s all right. I’ll be fine.

1310
01:29:31,869 --> 01:29:34,414
You will because
we'll call Señora Rodriguez.

1311
01:29:34,580 --> 01:29:38,960
-She owes me a favour. She has--
-I’m not calling Mrs. Rodriguez.

1312
01:29:39,127 --> 01:29:41,838
I love you, okay? I do.

1313
01:29:42,046 --> 01:29:44,882
But I don't want to clean houses.

1314
01:29:45,049 --> 01:29:47,176
There's nowhere to go from there.

1315
01:29:48,553 --> 01:29:53,850
Hasn't this taught you anything? Wake
up, little girl, you have responsibilities.

1316
01:29:54,017 --> 01:29:57,437
And they come every month
like clockwork.

1317
01:29:57,603 --> 01:29:59,689
You want to end up
back in the projects?

1318
01:29:59,897 --> 01:30:03,693
Keep dreaming dreams
that will never happen.

1319
01:30:03,860 --> 01:30:07,322
You want to put food on the table?
Call Señora Rodriguez.

1320
01:30:11,743 --> 01:30:14,037
You're right, Ma.

1321
01:30:14,245 --> 01:30:16,748
I’m a good cleaning lady.

1322
01:30:17,165 --> 01:30:20,168
I’ll start over.

1323
01:30:20,335 --> 01:30:22,337
But not with Mrs. Rodriguez.

1324
01:30:24,422 --> 01:30:27,592
I’m gonna find a job
as a maid in some hotel.

1325
01:30:27,759 --> 01:30:32,138
After some time passes, I’m gonna
apply for the management program.

1326
01:30:32,305 --> 01:30:35,224
And when I get the chance
to be a manager....

1327
01:30:35,391 --> 01:30:38,895
And I will, Ma. I know I will.

1328
01:30:39,103 --> 01:30:41,814
I’m going to take
that chance without any fear.

1329
01:30:41,981 --> 01:30:45,735
Without your voice
in my head telling me that I can't.

1330
01:30:51,491 --> 01:30:52,575
Did you see this?

1331
01:30:53,910 --> 01:30:56,079
-How did it start?
-Did he know you were a maid?

1332
01:30:56,287 --> 01:30:59,082
-Are you a Beresford perk?
-How long were you involved?

1333
01:30:59,290 --> 01:31:00,583
How did they find you out?

1334
01:31:00,792 --> 01:31:03,169
Any advice to other maids
looking to trade up?

1335
01:31:03,336 --> 01:31:06,047
-Did Democrats put you up to this?
-Does he tip well?

1336
01:31:06,214 --> 01:31:08,424
Is it true you're booked
on Larry King Live?

1337
01:31:08,633 --> 01:31:11,094
I'm at the Beresford Hotel,
where yesterday...

1338
01:31:11,302 --> 01:31:15,098
...Senate hopeful Chris Marshall was
captured on video in a lovers' spat...

1339
01:31:15,264 --> 01:31:18,184
...with a woman now identified
as a hotel maid.

1340
01:31:18,351 --> 01:31:19,894
Who's kidding who here?

1341
01:31:20,061 --> 01:31:23,064
Think you would've looked
at me if you knew I was the maid?

1342
01:31:23,231 --> 01:31:25,441
-With respect--
-Oh, shit.

1343
01:31:26,651 --> 01:31:27,819
Oh, my God.

1344
01:31:28,486 --> 01:31:30,571
We won't--
We will not be answering--

1345
01:31:30,738 --> 01:31:33,574
We will not be taking
any questions right now.

1346
01:31:33,741 --> 01:31:36,703
Mr. Marshall will make a statement.

1347
01:31:41,708 --> 01:31:43,459
Morning.

1348
01:31:43,626 --> 01:31:45,753
I’d like to make a short statement.

1349
01:31:45,920 --> 01:31:49,632
And it will be all
that I have to say about this....

1350
01:31:49,841 --> 01:31:53,136
This invasion of my privacy.

1351
01:31:55,346 --> 01:31:58,391
I happened to meet
Miss Ventura and her son...

1352
01:31:58,558 --> 01:32:04,522
...during my stay
at a hotel in New York.

1353
01:32:05,523 --> 01:32:07,817
And we became friends.

1354
01:32:10,028 --> 01:32:14,407
There are people from all walks
of life who I count as friends.

1355
01:32:14,574 --> 01:32:18,494
And my only regret in this instance
is that one of them, Miss Ventura...

1356
01:32:21,247 --> 01:32:24,500
...was subjected to the scrutiny
and innuendo of the media...

1357
01:32:24,709 --> 01:32:28,379
...as a result of that friendship with me.

1358
01:32:37,805 --> 01:32:41,893
I need these numbers
to be plus 10 percent.

1359
01:33:03,414 --> 01:33:05,875
Welcome to the employee cafeteria.

1360
01:33:08,836 --> 01:33:11,673
It’s open 24 hours a day....

1361
01:33:12,256 --> 01:33:14,008
Please.

1362
01:33:31,818 --> 01:33:33,903
Is today the 19th?

1363
01:33:34,112 --> 01:33:36,239
Six more shopping days.

1364
01:33:36,406 --> 01:33:38,032
He's here. He's back!

1365
01:33:38,199 --> 01:33:42,328
-Who? What are you reading?
-Yesterday's paper. Chris is in town.

1366
01:33:42,495 --> 01:33:44,914
So? Go put your clothes on.
It’s late.

1367
01:33:45,081 --> 01:33:47,458
So? He's giving a press conference.
Guess where?

1368
01:33:47,625 --> 01:33:51,254
I don't care. Okay? Come on.
Put your turtleneck on too. It’s cold.

1369
01:33:51,462 --> 01:33:52,964
At your hotel.

1370
01:33:53,131 --> 01:33:54,299
-Ma!
-What?

1371
01:33:54,465 --> 01:33:55,591
At your hotel!

1372
01:33:55,758 --> 01:33:57,927
I heard you, bubba!

1373
01:33:58,136 --> 01:34:02,056
Don't you think it's weird?
You'll be there, he'll be there.

1374
01:34:02,849 --> 01:34:05,727
So will a thousand other people.
We talked about this.

1375
01:34:05,893 --> 01:34:08,354
You have your
turtleneck on backwards.

1376
01:34:08,521 --> 01:34:10,273
I thought we talked about this.

1377
01:34:10,773 --> 01:34:12,442
I know, but it's like fate.

1378
01:34:12,608 --> 01:34:17,238
No, it's like New York City
and an available conference room.

1379
01:34:17,405 --> 01:34:19,115
You knew, didn't you?

1380
01:34:19,324 --> 01:34:22,327
You weren't gonna tell me.
You knew he was coming.

1381
01:34:22,493 --> 01:34:26,581
Remember, bubba, what I told you?
We talked about this.

1382
01:34:26,998 --> 01:34:31,044
He's not part of our lives,
but we wish him luck with his, right?

1383
01:34:32,003 --> 01:34:33,296
You think he misses us?

1384
01:34:38,217 --> 01:34:41,220
Well, he'd be crazy not to.

1385
01:35:04,661 --> 01:35:07,538
Mr. Marshall, if elected,
you'll be the third Marshall...

1386
01:35:07,705 --> 01:35:10,833
...to serve New York in the Senate.
How does it feel?

1387
01:35:11,000 --> 01:35:13,336
lf I get elected, I’ll let you know.

1388
01:35:15,213 --> 01:35:17,090
Did your father
leave you any advice?

1389
01:35:17,256 --> 01:35:20,635
Yeah, he said, “Don't run.”

1390
01:35:21,886 --> 01:35:24,013
We have time
for one more question, folks.

1391
01:35:24,222 --> 01:35:26,641
Then we have
a meet-and-greet in the Green Room.

1392
01:35:26,808 --> 01:35:28,768
I have a question.

1393
01:35:29,978 --> 01:35:34,649
-What? Who said that?
-Mr. Marshall, down here.

1394
01:35:36,025 --> 01:35:37,485
Sure.

1395
01:35:37,694 --> 01:35:40,029
What's your question?

1396
01:35:41,572 --> 01:35:42,657
I was wondering....

1397
01:35:42,824 --> 01:35:46,119
-Chris, don't do this.
-No. Wait. I’m listening. Go ahead.

1398
01:35:46,285 --> 01:35:47,370
Well....

1399
01:35:48,413 --> 01:35:51,165
I know everyone makes mistakes.

1400
01:35:51,332 --> 01:35:55,837
And it's a sign of character to give
a person a second chance, right?

1401
01:35:56,004 --> 01:35:58,715
Right. I’m with you.

1402
01:36:00,091 --> 01:36:04,137
Even if someone lied,
they should be forgiven.

1403
01:36:04,304 --> 01:36:07,557
Otherwise, we'd never have
any congressmen or presidents.

1404
01:36:09,600 --> 01:36:11,853
Thanks very much.
We have to wrap this up.

1405
01:36:12,020 --> 01:36:14,522
Jerry, he's not done. Go on.

1406
01:36:14,731 --> 01:36:20,320
Well, what if you're not a politician
trying to do good for everybody?

1407
01:36:20,486 --> 01:36:23,865
What if you're just a regular person,
like a maid or something?

1408
01:36:26,034 --> 01:36:28,661
And she made a mistake.

1409
01:36:29,287 --> 01:36:31,706
Do you think she should
get a second chance?

1410
01:36:31,873 --> 01:36:33,708
I mean, nobody's perfect, right?

1411
01:36:34,667 --> 01:36:38,254
No. Nobody's perfect.

1412
01:36:39,005 --> 01:36:42,508
Ladies and gentlemen of the press,
take a look at a future candidate.

1413
01:36:43,468 --> 01:36:47,096
All right, thanks very much, folks.
We'll see you all in Buffalo.

1414
